        "# Are hectare acre {.hiddenheading #sec-aha}\n",
        "\n",
        "A square [kilozem]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"a thousand zems\"} ([kz&sup2;](#kz2){#squarekilozem .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"square kilozem\"}) is 1 [hexakilare]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"sixteen hundred ares\"}, 16 [hectares](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#:~:text=a%20square%20with%20100%2Dmetre%20sides){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"hundreds of ares\"}, 1600 [ares](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hectare#Are), 40 Dec [acres](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acre#:~:text=%20is-,a%20unit%20of%20land%20area,-used%20in%20the), 0.16 square [kilometers](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kilometre#:~:text=a%20unit%20of%20length%20in%20the%20International%20System%20of%20Units){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"thousands of meters\"} ([km&sup2;](#km2){#squarekilometer .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"square kilometers\"}), 0.0625 Dec [square miles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_mile#:~:text=US%20unit%20of%20measure%20for%20area), [10^6^]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"a million\"} [z&sup2;](#z2){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"square zems\"}, or 1 megahexamilliare ([Mx](#Mx){#megahexamilliare .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"megahexamilliare\"}). A [z&sup2;](#z2){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"square zem\"} is 1 [hexamilliare]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"1.6 thousandths of an are\"} ([x](#x){#hexamilliare .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"hexamilliare\"}), 16 square [decimeters]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"tenths of a meter\"} ([dm&sup2;](#dm2){#squaredecimeter .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"square decimeters\"}), 1.[7]{.vinculum} Dec [square feet](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_foot#:~:text=the%20area%20of%20a%20square%20with%20sides%20of%201%20foot)🦶 ([f&sup2;](#f2){#squarefoot .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"square feet\"}), or 256 Dec square inches ([i&sup2;](#i2){#squareinch .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"square inch\"}). A square [decazem]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"ten zem\"} ([Dz&sup2;](#Dz2){#squaredecazem .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"square decazem\"}) is 1 [hexadeciare]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"sixteen hundredths of an are\"}, 16 [square meters](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_metre#:~:text=the%20unit%20of%20area%20in%20the%20International%20System%20of%20Units) ([m&sup2;](#m2){#squaremeter .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"square meters\"}), [~]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"approximately\"}19.75 Dec [square yards](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_yard#:~:text=U.S.%20customary%20unit%20of%20area), or 100 [x](#x){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"hexamilliares\"}.\n",
