        "# Drop wineglass keg {.hiddenheading #sec-dwk}\n",
        "\n",
        "A cubic [decizem]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"a tenth of a zone equatorial meter\"} ([dz&sup3;](#dz3){#cubicdecizem .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"cubic decizem\"}) is 1 cubic [nanotaur]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"a millionth of a taur\"} ([nc&sup3;](#nc3){#cubicnanotaur .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"cubic nanotaur\"}), 1 Dec wineglass, 2 Dec ounces, 64 [milliliters]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"thousandths of a liter\"} ([mL](#mL){#milliliter .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"milliliters\"}), 1000 Dec drops ([g](#g){#gutta .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"drops\"}), or 1000 cubic [centizems]{.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"a tenth of a zone equatorial meter\"} ([cz&sup3;](#cz3){#cubiccentizem .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"cubic centizem\"}). A [dz&sup3;](#dz3){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"cubic decizem\"} of water🌊weighs $1\\over7$ Dec pounds, 64 grams, or 1000 Dec grains ([g](#g){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"grain\"}). A Dec ounce ([u](#u){#ounce .tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"ounce\"}) of water weighs $1\\over14$ Dec pounds, 500 Dec [g](#g){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"grains\"}, or 32 grams. In Dec, the symbols [g](#g){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"grain\"} and [u](#u){.tool data-bs-toggle=\"tooltip\" data-bs-title=\"ounce\"} can refer to either volume or mass. Mass divided by volume is density.\n",
